text: Engelier is located lower left on this image. Engelier is a 310-mile (500-kilometers) large crater on Saturn's moon Iapetus in Saragossa Terra. It partially obscures the slightly smaller crater Gerin. == See also == *List of geological features on Iapetus ==Notes== Category:Impact craters on Saturn's moons Category:Surface features of Iapetus (moon)
title: Engelier
